Just curious, are the individual minor leaguers more scarce than the major leaguers? I have only been accumulating major leagues players thus far.

Hi!

A Minor Leaguer T205 is MUCH harder to find than a COMMON Major Leaguer.  They were issued as part of this set very late in its production (late 1911 probably).

There are A NUMBER of threads in the archives here that help to explain their scarcity (and other cards in this set) and it is worth your time to find and read them, if interested.

I have collected this set for a number of years, but won't pretend to be anywhere near as knowledgeable as many of the folks who post here!

EXCELLENT question - GOOD LUCK On your search...as long as you are NOT looking for the same cards that I am!!!  :D:D:D
